Nigerians on Twitter are dragging presidential aide, Bashir Ahamd, after he came out to complain about his bank app. According to report , Bashir took to his Twitter handle to berate a commercial bank for their ”super useless” app. He wrote; ”I don’t know whether it’s only happening to me, but Zenith Bank App has been super useless since after upgrading it, I have been trying to use the App since morning and still not successful. @ZenithBank  fix your App.” Angry Nigerians took to his comment section to drag him for coming online to complain. According to them, Bashir has no right to describe the bank as useless. Some said he needs to feel the pain Nigerians have been going through since the Buhari-led government took over office in 2015.     By Chibuike Nwabuko Abuja (Sundiata Post) - Group under the auspices of Human Rights Writers Association of Nigeria, HURIWA, has asked President Muhammadu Buhari to dismiss his Assistant on New Media, Bashir Ahmad for making derogatory and contemptuous comments at the Federal High Court. Recall that following the sentencing of… In "Top Stories" The Nigeria Centre for Disease Control (NCDC) on Sunday April 19, confirmed eighty six new cases of Coronavirus bringing the total number to 627, and this got mixed reactions from Nigerians. After the news was shared on Twitter, singer Zlatan reacted to the post with laughing emojis. Presidential aide, Bashir… In "News" •CEO IPI, Adamu Garba says he requested google to unpublish his App to correct some bugs, findings reveal the claim is not misleading Mohammed Dahiru Lawal Claim: The Chief Executive Officer, IPI Group, Adamu Garba, says he asked Google to take down his social media platform, Crowwe App, from Google… In "Technology"